 * @endcode
 *
 * @subsection dependencies_libsodium_bcrypt libsodium-bcrypt-pbkdf
 *
 * **Purpose**: OpenSSH private key decryption (bcrypt-pbkdf KDF)
 *
 * **Repository**: https://github.com/Tarsnap/libsodium-bcrypt
 *
 * **License**: BSD License
 *
 * **Version**: Git submodule at deps/libsodium-bcrypt-pbkdf
 *
 * **Integration**: Compiled as part of ascii-chat-crypto library
 *
 * **Key Features**:
 * - bcrypt-pbkdf key derivation function (OpenSSH standard)
 * - Decrypts password-protected SSH Ed25519 private keys
 * - Uses libsodium for underlying primitives
 * - Constant-time operations
 *
 * **Usage in ascii-chat**:
 * - `lib/crypto/keys/ssh_keys.c` - SSH private key decryption
 * - Decrypts modern OpenSSH private key format (RFC 4253)
 * - Supports passphrase-protected keys with bcrypt-pbkdf KDF
 *
 * **Why This Dependency?**:
 * - OpenSSH uses bcrypt-pbkdf for key encryption (not standard PBKDF2)
 * - libsodium doesn't include bcrypt-pbkdf natively
 * - This is the reference implementation from OpenSSH
 * - Required for full SSH key compatibility
 *
 * **Security Properties**:
 * - Memory-hard KDF resistant to GPU/ASIC attacks
 * - Configurable rounds for computational cost
 * - Standard for OpenSSH encrypted private keys
 *
 * @section dependencies_testing Testing Dependencies
 *
 * These dependencies are only required for building and running tests.
 * They are not needed for normal ascii-chat operation.
 *
 * @subsection dependencies_criterion Criterion - Testing Framework
 *
 * **Purpose**: Comprehensive unit, integration, and performance testing
 *
 * **Website**: https://criterion.readthedocs.io/
 *
 * **License**: MIT License
 *
 * **Version**: 2.4.0 or later
 *
 * **Platform Support**: POSIX systems (Linux, macOS)
 *
 * **Key Features**:
 * - Automatic test discovery and registration
 * - Fixtures with setup/teardown hooks
 * - Parameterized tests with theories
 * - Timeout and signal safety
 * - TAP and JUnit XML output formats
 * - Memory leak detection integration
 * - Beautiful test output with colors
 *
 * **Usage in ascii-chat**:
 * - `tests/unit/` - Unit tests for individual components
 * - `tests/integration/` - Integration tests for multi-component workflows
 * - `tests/performance/` - Performance benchmarks and SIMD validation
 *
 * **Test Categories**:
 * - **Unit Tests**: Component isolation testing (buffer_pool, packet_queue, etc.)
 * - **Integration Tests**: Multi-component workflows (client-server handshake, etc.)
 * - **Performance Tests**: SIMD vs scalar benchmarks with speedup validation
 *
 * **Configuration**:
 * @code{.cmake}
 * pkg_check_modules(CRITERION criterion)
 * if(CRITERION_FOUND)
 *   enable_testing()
 *   add_test(NAME unit_tests COMMAND test_unit_all)
 * endif()
 * @endcode
 *
 * **Windows Note**:
 * - Criterion is POSIX-based and doesn't work natively on Windows
 * - Windows tests must be run via Docker container
 * - Use `tests/scripts/run-docker-tests.ps1` for Windows testing
 *
 * @section dependencies_optional Optional Dependencies
 *
 * These dependencies enhance ascii-chat functionality but are not strictly
 * required. The application gracefully degrades when they are unavailable.
 *
 * @subsection dependencies_mimalloc mimalloc - High-Performance Allocator
 *
 * **Purpose**: Fast memory allocation for production builds
 *
 * **Website**: https://github.com/microsoft/mimalloc
 *
 * **License**: MIT License
 *
 * **Version**: 2.0.0 or later
 *
 * **Availability**: Optional, enabled with `-DUSE_MIMALLOC=ON`
 *
 * **Key Features**:
 * - Up to 2x faster than system malloc/free
 * - Better memory locality and cache performance
 * - Lower memory fragmentation
 * - Optimized for multi-threaded workloads
 * - Drop-in replacement for malloc/free
 *
 * **Usage in ascii-chat**:
 * - Used in release builds (`release`, `release-clang`, `relwithdebinfo`)
 * - Overrides system malloc/free/realloc
 * - Transparent to application code
 *
 * **Performance Benefits**:
 * - Faster audio buffer allocation/deallocation
 * - Reduced memory fragmentation in long-running servers
 * - Better cache locality for video frame buffers
 * - Improved performance under multi-client load
 *
 * **Configuration**:
 * @code{.cmake}
 * option(USE_MIMALLOC "Use mimalloc allocator" OFF)
 * if(USE_MIMALLOC)
 *   find_library(MIMALLOC_LIB mimalloc)
 *   target_link_libraries(ascii-chat PRIVATE ${MIMALLOC_LIB})
 * endif()
 * @endcode
 *
 * @section dependencies_platform Platform APIs (Zero External Dependencies)
 *
 * ascii-chat uses native platform APIs for webcam access, eliminating the
 * need for heavy dependencies like OpenCV.
 *
 * @subsection dependencies_platform_video Video Capture APIs
 *
 * **Linux - Video4Linux2 (V4L2)**:
 * - Kernel module interface (no library dependency)
 * - Direct ioctl() calls to `/dev/video*` devices
 * - Implementation: `lib/webcam_v4l2.c`
 * - Supports MJPEG and YUYV formats
 * - Zero-copy mmap() for performance
 *
 * **macOS - AVFoundation**:
 * - Native macOS multimedia framework
 * - Objective-C implementation: `lib/webcam_avfoundation.m`
 * - System framework (no external dependency)
 * - Hardware-accelerated format conversion
 * - Supports all connected cameras
 *
 * **Windows - Media Foundation**:
 * - Native Windows multimedia API
 * - Implementation: `lib/webcam_windows.c`
 * - System library (no external dependency)
 * - COM-based interface
 * - Future enhancement (currently test pattern mode)
 *
 * @subsection dependencies_platform_terminal Terminal APIs
 *
 * **POSIX - termios**:
 * - Standard POSIX terminal control
 * - Implementation: `lib/platform/posix/terminal.c`
 * - Raw mode, non-blocking I/O
 * - ANSI escape sequence support
 *
 * **Windows - Console API**:
 * - Native Windows Console API
 * - Implementation: `lib/platform/windows/terminal.c`
 * - Virtual terminal sequences (Windows 10+)
 * - UTF-16 to UTF-8 conversion
 *
