 * @subsection dependencies_cmake CMake - Build System Generator
 *
 * **Version**: 3.20 or later
 *
 * **Purpose**: Cross-platform build system configuration
 *
 * **Features Used**:
 * - CMake Presets for build configurations
 * - Modern target-based dependency management
 * - Cross-compilation support
 * - Automatic dependency detection
 *
 * @subsection dependencies_ninja Ninja - Build System
 *
 * **Version**: 1.10 or later
 *
 * **Purpose**: Fast parallel compilation
 *
 * **Benefits**:
 * - Automatic CPU core detection and parallelization
 * - Minimal build overhead
 * - Incremental builds with dependency tracking
 * - 2-3x faster than Make on multi-core systems
 *
 * @subsection dependencies_clang Clang/LLVM - C Compiler and Toolchain
 *
 * **Version**: 12.0 or later
 *
 * **Purpose**: Primary compiler for all platforms
 *
 * **Features Used**:
 * - C23 standard support
 * - AddressSanitizer for memory debugging
 * - UndefinedBehaviorSanitizer for UB detection
 * - clang-format for code formatting
 * - clang-tidy for static analysis
 * - SIMD intrinsics (SSE2, AVX2, NEON)
 *
 * **Why Clang?**:
 * - Better error messages than GCC
 * - Consistent behavior across platforms
 * - Superior sanitizer support
 * - Integrated tooling (format, tidy)
 * - Native Windows support (no MinGW needed)
 *
